?\n<Tim>

Excuse me.\n<Serena>
...\n<Boy>
Excuse me, shopkeeper.\n<Serena>
...Ahahaha! Oh no, a customer... I'm sorry!\n<Boy>
Shopkeeper, I'd like to sell a book.\n<Serena>

Oh, I-I'm sorry. I-I'm not the shopkeeper, just
the clerk...\n<Boy>
Hm? Is that so? Then where is the shopkeeper...\n<Serena>

They've gone out to procure goods and won't be
back for a while...\n<Boy>
Is that so... Hmm...\n<Serena>

Oh, are you looking to sell? If it's listed in the
catalog, I can offer you a price...\n<Boy>
Is that so? It's this book here...\n<Serena>

Wow, it's in the original language... Uh, the
title is... "The Freedom of Natural Instinct"...
maybe?\n<Boy>
The original language is only on the cover.\n<Serena>

Oh, you're right... and there's so much writing
inside...\n<Boy>
Would it be difficult to sell?\n<Serena>

No, this is quite normal. It's rarer to find a
book that's brand new...\n<Boy>

But um... I'm sorry, it seems this book isn't
listed in our catalog...\n<Boy>

If the manager were here, they might be able to
set a price for it...\n<Boy>

I see... Well, I wasn't expecting much. If you
can't buy it, that's fine.\n<Serena>
You seem a bit happy about that.\n<Boy>
N-No, that's not it at all.\n<Serena>
Do you like books?\n<Boy>

Yes. Books are good. They nourish the brain. A
good book is like a fine meal.\n<Serena>

Ehehe, you say such nice things. My own theory is
that books are edible.\n<Boy>

It seems we have similar tastes. My name is
Serena. I'm an adventurer.\n<Serena>
Oh, what do we have here. My name is Tim.\n<Tim>

I'm sort of an adventurer too. I'm not good with
rough stuff, so I mostly take on these kinds of
errands...\n<Tim>

Is that so? Then perhaps we've crossed paths at
the guild without knowing it.\n<Serena>

Well, I wonder about that. I don't really like the
atmosphere there... I try to avoid going if I
can...\n<Tim>

Haha, I feel the same way. The atmosphere there
isn't great. First off, the air is bad. And the
lighting too.\n<Serena>
It feels like an adult's world, doesn't it?\n<Tim>

Bad adults... Ah, we've ended up talking about
nothing of substance.\n<Serena>

Sorry, but I must hurry along. It was enjoyable
but I can't stay and chat for long.\n<Serena>

Is that so? You seem to have quite the belly on
you... must be tough...\n<Tim>
Yes... well, there's that too...\n<Serena>

If you don't mind, please come again. Pregnant
women can't move around much, right? Books could
surely be of help to you.\n<Tim>
Is that so? That's a shame.\n<Tim>

If you'd like, please come again. The manager
won't be back for a while, but we're always
updating our stock of books...\n<Tim>

If you love books, I think you'll enjoy our
store... that's what I believe, anyway...\n<Tim>

Hmm. If I find the time, I'll make sure to stop by
again.\n<Serena>
Then, Tim-dono, I shall take my leave.\n<Serena>
Whew... that surprised me.\n<Tim>
What a cute girl she is. Eyes as red as rubies.\n<Tim>
Serena-chan, huh...\n<Tim>
I wonder if she'll come again...\n<Tim>

Now, it's about time to return to the brothel. I
wonder what this new job will entail...\n<Serena>
